According to the [Bamboo variables|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO/Bamboo+variables] documentation, the following variable should display the id of the agent that the deployment is executed on.
{code:title=Script task}
echo "bamboo.agentID: ${bamboo.agentID}"
{code}
{code}
15-Aug-2014 14:13:03	/var/folders/69/yqtz3vys3gq_z68gt9yydc240000gn/T/1671169-1736705-2097159-ScriptBuildTask-2423268153105686424.sh: line 1: bamboo.agentID: ${bamboo.agentID}: bad substitution
{code}

After adding a requirement to a Job, the message text changes from
{noformat}
This job can only be built by agents whose capabilities meet the 0 requirements below
{noformat}
to
{noformat}
This job can only be built by agents whose capabilities meet the {0} requirement below
{noformat}
Adding another requirements changes the text correctly to
{noformat}
This job can only be built by agents whose capabilities meet the 2 requirements below
{noformat}

The {{"\{0\}"}} should be replaced by {{"1"}}

Hi guys,

I just want you make aware of a API breakage in Bamboo 5.6 which happened without deprecating the previous method first. That's slighly sub-optimal.

Breakage happened in commit [ee24076|https://stash.atlassian.com/projects/BAM/repos/bamboo/commits/ee24076]. The concrete change is [here|https://stash.atlassian.com/projects/BAM/repos/bamboo/commits/ee24076#components/bamboo-api/src/main/java/com/atlassian/bamboo/build/artifact/ArtifactLinkDataProvider.java]:
{noformat}
@@ -7,8 +7,11 @@ import java.util.Date;
 
 public interface ArtifactLinkDataProvider
 {
+    @Nullable
+    String getRootUrl();
+
     @NotNull
-    Iterable<String> getUrls();
+    Iterable<ArtifactFileData> listObjects(@Nullable final String subpath);
 
     @Nullable
     Date lastModified();
{noformat}

{code}
Scenario:
1. Bamboo build produces artifacts and generates a custom software version as a combination of our string and ${bamboo.BuildNumber}  - in this scenario we generate a Microsoft-like version, e.g. 21.1.21.43 - (1.jpg attached)
2. Use Bamboo "Inject Variable" plugin to inject this version into build results (1.jpg attached)
3. Enable the Deployment Project to use this ${bamboo.inject.myVariable} to set as a Release Version (2.jpg) - currently it doesn't understand this variable. (3.jpg attached)
{code}

On OnDemand we've seen several cases of Agents staying online even though their associated instance is no longer available. However their licenses are not freed up, preventing new instances from being started. If a new instance is started the agent will not load and the following message is given to the user on the Elastic Images page:
{quote}
Registration of elastic agent at instance i-####### failed with a message: Cannot register additional elastic agent. You have reached the limit for the number of remote agents you can have. Please upgrade your license.
{quote}

