It would be great if Bamboo UI detailed errors when improper DB encoding was selected.

From our customer:
{quote}
When I used "localhost" for the MySQL domain it tried to connect to 127.0.0.1 instead which failed authenticate because the user was granted access on localhost. I found this out by reviewing the catalina.out file. It would have been nice to see the error on the webpage. Instead it just redirected me back to the database configuration page without any errors.
{quote}

I was able to duplicate/confirm this behavior in 5.5.1.
